claim.claim-text:
1. A graphical symbol apparatus for use on a display system used by an operator in an aerial refueling operation between an airborne tanker vehicle and an airborne receiver vehicle, the apparatus comprising:
a receiver graphic representing said receiver vehicle and moveable in accordance with a position of said receiver vehicle;
a boom graphic having a length that changes and is scaled in accordance with telescoping movement of a refueling boom;
a contact zone graphic indicating an area in which contact can be made between said refueling boom and said receiver vehicle; and
said receiver graphic and said boom graphic providing a visual representation of when said refueling boom and said receiver vehicle are in position for contact to be made between said refueling boom and a refueling receptacle of said receiving vehicle.

11. A graphical symbol apparatus for use on a display system used by an operator in an aerial refueling operation between an airborne tanker vehicle and an airborne receiver vehicle, the apparatus comprising:
a contact zone graphic representing a desired contact zone within which contact between a refueling boom of said refueling vehicle and a refueling receptacle of said refueling vehicle can be made;
a receiver graphic representing said receiver vehicle and moveable in accordance with a position of said receiver vehicle, said movement of said receiver graphic further being scaled in accordance with a sensed speed of said receiver vehicle;
a boom graphic modified in accordance with telescoping movement of said refueling boom; and
said receiver graphic and said boom graphic providing a visual representation of when said refueling boom and said receiver vehicle are in position within said contact zone for contact to be made between said refueling boom and said refueling receptacle; and
wherein an edge portion of said receiver graphic contacts an edge portion of said boom graphic when a tip of said refueling boom has made contact with a refueling receptacle of said receiver vehicle.

18. A graphical symbol apparatus for use on a display system used by an operator in an aerial refueling operation between an airborne tanker vehicle and an airborne receiver vehicle, the apparatus comprising:
a contact zone graphic representing a desired contact zone, relative to said refueling vehicle, within which contact between a refueling boom of said refueling vehicle and a refueling receptacle of said refueling vehicle can be made;
a receiver graphic representing said receiver vehicle and moveable linearly in accordance with a position of said receiver vehicle, relative to said contact zone, said movement of said receiver graphic further being scaled in accordance with a sensed speed of said receiver vehicle;
a boom graphic scaled in dimension in accordance with telescoping movement of said refueling boom and linearly aligned with said contact zone graphic;
said receiver graphic and said boom graphic providing a visual representation of when said refueling boom and said receiver vehicle are in position within said contact zone for contact to be made between said refueling boom and said refueling receptacle; and
wherein contact between an edge portion of said receiver graphic and an edge portion of said boom graphic indicates that said refueling boom has made contact with said refueling receptacle of said receiver vehicle.
